<h2>Terms of Use</h2>
<p>Stemming.org provides no warranty as to anything! We're just a website.</p>
<p>Information and content that users provide to stemming.org on their profile page or in blog posts remains property of the users; however, the website stemming.org is granted a non-exclusive license to use and reprint this content in perpetuity.</p>
<p>If a user contacts us with a request that information be removed from our site, we will make a good-faith effort to do so; however, we cannot guarantee that information can be removed once it has been entered into the site.</p>
<p>Stemming.org reserves the right to delete any content than an administrator deems inappropriate for the site.</p>
<p>Stemming.org also reserves the right to delete any user account without notice at the sole discretion of the administrator.</p>
<p>In compliance with <a href="http://www.coppa.org">the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act</a>, we cannot allow users under the age of 13 to join, and we will delete any account that appears to belong to a child under 13.</p>
<p>These terms are subject to change without notice.</p>

</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>Privacy</h2>
<p>Users provide stemming.org with their personal email address upon signup. We will use this email address to send users relevant information about their use of the site; we will also share this email address with other users when the user sends a "contact" request.</p>
<p>Email addresses are not displayed publicly and will never be sold or shared with anyone outside of users of stemming.org.</p>
<p>Personal information that users enter into their profile, blog posts, comments, or elsewhere on the site is displayed publicly.</p> 
